## Rules content

### Scope and boundaries

Apply when adding or changing UI, layout, navigation chrome, or page files under **`web-app/`** — presentation only; no domain persistence or business rules in page containers beyond client validation and thin adapters.

- Knowledge: **`web-app/`** is presentation-only per **`.cursor/rules/solution/solution.mdc`** — domain logic stays in `*.svc/` microservices; this file is authoritative for **`web-app/`** layout only — for **`aspire.svc/`** use **`aspire.svc/.cursor/rules/nextjs.mdc`** and **`pages_compoents_style_guide.mdc`**, not this file.
- Rule: **`web-app/app/api/**`** route handlers validate input and delegate to gRPC or adapters only — no domain rules, persistence, or authz decisions in handlers.
- Rule: Do not copy layout, CSS, gradients, or nav patterns from **`aspire.svc/`**, **`frontend/`**, **`bu-analytics-gen-ai-midas/frontend`**, or other monorepo apps unless the user explicitly requests it — reuse product copy only when asked.
- Rule: Use semantic EXL theme tokens from **`web-app/app/globals.css`** — `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, `text-primary`, `shadow-surface` — never hard-code hex or orange literals when a token exists.
- Rule: Use shadcn/ui primitives from **`web-app/components/ui/`** — add new primitives via **`web-app/components.json`** before inventing bespoke controls.
- Knowledge: Long-form junior guide — **`doc/web-design.md`**; page file tree and shells — **`doc/web-app-pages.md`**.

### Three-layer responsive architecture

Responsive behavior is split into shells, layout primitives, and page content — page authors work mostly in Layer 3.

- Knowledge: **Layer 1 — shells** — `DashboardShell` (`web-app/components/layout/dashboard-shell.tsx`); **`MarketingPageShell`** + **`MarketingHeader`** (`web-app/components/layout/marketing-page-shell.tsx`, `marketing-header.tsx`); **`AuthPageLayout`** / **`AuthPanel`** (`web-app/pages-components/user/components/auth-page-layout.tsx`); template inner chrome **`TemplatesPageLayout`**, **`TemplateGroupPageLayout`**, **`CodeDemoSection`** (`web-app/pages-components/templates/components/`).
- Knowledge: **Layer 2 — layout primitives** — target paths **`web-app/components/layout/responsive/`** and **`web-app/lib/responsive/`** for `PageSection`, `ResponsiveGrid`, show/hide helpers — use standard class patterns from **`doc/web-design.md`** until primitives exist.
- Knowledge: **Layer 3 — page content** — one **`page-container.tsx`** per route under **`web-app/pages-components/<area>/<page>/components/`** owns forms, cards, copy, and section subcomponents only.
- Rule: Never create separate page components or subfolders per viewport (`smartphone/`, `tablet/`, `laptop/`, `desktop/`) — one URL, one page-container, CSS breakpoints adapt layout.
- Rule: Global navigation, sidebar, and mobile menu behavior belong in **Layer 1 shells only** — not in individual `page-container.tsx` files.
- Rule: Page max-width, horizontal padding, and standard grid column presets belong in **Layer 2 primitives** or the documented standard classes — avoid ad-hoc duplication across every page long term.

### Four viewport targets and Tailwind breakpoints

Design and implement for four ranges using mobile-first Tailwind defaults aligned with **`doc/web-design.md`** section 1.3.

- Knowledge: Tables in this subsection are reference material for breakpoint mapping only.

| Target | Width | Tailwind | Layout notes |
|--------|-------|----------|--------------|
| Smartphone | below 640px | default (no prefix) | Single column, stacked actions, compact header, touch-friendly controls |
| Tablet | 640px – 1023px | `sm:`, `md:` | Increased padding; 2-column grids where appropriate |
| Laptop | 1024px – 1279px | `lg:` | Workspace sidebar; auth two-column (copy + form) |
| Desktop | 1280px and up | `xl:` | Wider max-width (`xl:max-w-7xl`); denser multi-column grids |

- Rule: Tailwind is mobile-first — unprefixed classes apply to smartphone; prefixed classes apply at that min-width and above — start single-column, add columns at `sm:` / `xl:` rather than desktop-first overrides.
- Rule: Prefer **`default`**, **`sm:`**, **`md:`**, **`lg:`**, **`xl:`** — use **`2xl:`** only when design explicitly requires extra width above 1280px.
- Rule: Use responsive CSS grids (`grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3`) — not fixed pixel column widths on cards or panels.
- Action: When implementing or reviewing a page, mentally verify all four targets in section table — smartphone default, tablet padding/grids, laptop shell behaviors, desktop max-width and third grid column.

### Layout shells — which shell and viewport duties

Pick exactly one shell per page type — never mount auth or template gallery pages inside **`DashboardShell`**.

- Knowledge: Shell selection table — workspace **`app/pages/(workspace)/**`** → **`DashboardShell`**; marketing root **`app/page.tsx`** → **`MarketingPageShell`**; user/auth **`app/pages/user/**`** → **`MarketingPageShell`** at layout with **`AuthPageLayout`** inside page containers; templates **`app/pages/templates/**`** → **`MarketingPageShell`** + **`TemplatesPageLayout`**.

- Rule: **`DashboardShell`** — smartphone/tablet: sidebar hidden by default, opened via menu button in sheet/drawer; laptop/desktop: persistent sidebar — implement drawer in shell when missing, do not patch per page.
- Rule: **`MarketingPageShell`** / **`MarketingHeader`** — smartphone: compact header with hamburger → sheet for primary nav; laptop/desktop: full horizontal nav — never hide nav on mobile without a sheet alternative.
- Rule: **`AuthPageLayout`** — smartphone/tablet: single centered column; laptop/desktop: two columns with `aside` visible at `lg:` (`hidden lg:flex` on aside, `lg:grid` on section) — follow existing **`auth-page-layout.tsx`** pattern.
- Rule: Template gallery pages use **`MarketingPageShell`** at **`app/pages/templates/layout.tsx`** with **`TemplatesHeaderTrailing`** in the header trailing slot — inner content uses **`TemplatesPageLayout`** and **`TemplateGroupPageLayout`** / **`CodeDemoSection`** — do not duplicate marketing header or gallery URL chrome inside page containers.
- Rule: Shell chrome dimensions are shared — marketing and workspace headers **`h-14`** (56 px); sidebar widths and drawer behavior live in **`web-app/components/layout/`** and layout CSS variables — do not override header height or sidebar width per page.
- Action: When adding a new route, confirm shell from **`doc/web-app-pages.md`** section 3 before writing **`page-container.tsx`**.

### Marketing shell and header

Apply when building or changing marketing home, user/auth routes, or template gallery — one shared header component, never reimplemented per page.

- Knowledge: **`MarketingHeader`** — **`web-app/components/layout/marketing-header.tsx`** — EXL logo, **`DECISION_AI_NAME`** from **`web-app/pages-components/shared/decision-ai-brand.ts`**, optional center **`navigationItems`**, optional **`trailing`** slot, default Sign in / Register actions via **`showAuthActions`** (default true).
- Knowledge: **`MarketingPageShell`** — **`web-app/components/layout/marketing-page-shell.tsx`** — wraps **`MarketingHeader`** + **`<main>`** + optional **`footer`**; used by **`app/page.tsx`** (home), **`app/pages/user/layout.tsx`**, and **`app/pages/templates/layout.tsx`**.
- Knowledge: Template routes pass **`headerTrailing={<TemplatesHeaderTrailing />}`** — **`web-app/pages-components/templates/components/templates-header-trailing.tsx`** — gallery link + **`TemplatesIndexUrlBadge`** (`templates-index-url-badge.tsx`); group pages still use in-content back link via **`TemplatesPageLayout`** with **`showBackLink`**.
- Rule: Never copy-paste header JSX into **`home-page.tsx`**, template page containers, or auth page containers — extend **`MarketingHeader`** / **`MarketingPageShell`** or pass **`trailing`** / **`navigationItems`** props from the route layout.
- Rule: Marketing header inner bar uses the same width/padding as page content — **`max-w-6xl xl:max-w-7xl`**, **`px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`**, sticky **`h-14`**, **`border-b border-border`**, **`bg-background/80 backdrop-blur-md`**, **`z-(--z-header)`**.
- Rule: Product display name on public marketing surfaces is **`Decision.AI`** via **`DECISION_AI_NAME`** — do not hard-code **`ARB - AI Assistant`** or other legacy strings on marketing/auth/template chrome unless **`app-config-public`** is updated deliberately.
- Rule: Reuse **text or product copy** from other monorepo apps (e.g. **`bu-analytics-gen-ai-midas/frontend`**) only when the user explicitly requests it — never import their layout, gradients, nav, or button styling.
- Rule: Home marketing footer is passed as **`MarketingPageShell`** **`footer`** prop from **`pages-components/home/home-page.tsx`** — auth and template layouts omit footer unless a page explicitly needs one.


Use shared spacing, width, grid, and visibility patterns — prefer future **`PageSection`** / **`ResponsiveGrid`** components when present.

- Rule: Standard page outer container classes — `mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 sm:py-10 md:py-12 lg:px-8 xl:max-w-7xl` — unless a primitive wraps them.
- Rule: **Cards grid preset** — `grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3` for card lists (dashboard, template index pattern).
- Rule: Show block from laptop — `hidden lg:flex` or `hidden lg:block`; hide on laptop+ — `lg:hidden`; show from tablet — `hidden md:flex` — for UI blocks, not whole pages.
- Rule: Responsive typography — page titles `text-2xl sm:text-3xl` (optional `lg:text-4xl`); body `text-sm sm:text-base`; hero `text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl` — limit to 2–3 steps per element.
- Rule: If **`web-app/components/layout/responsive/`** exports **`PageSection`**, **`ResponsiveGrid`**, **`ShowFrom`**, or **`HideFrom`**, use those instead of re-pasting the full standard class strings on new pages.
- Action: When introducing repeated outer layout classes on a third page, prefer adding or extending a primitive in **`web-app/components/layout/responsive/`** over copy-paste.

### Mandatory page file structure

Every page uses thin route + page entry + page container — never skip the container or put UI in **`app/**/page.tsx`**.

- Rule: **`app/**/page.tsx`** — thin route only: default export named **`XxxRoute`** renders **`<XxxPage />`** — forbidden: `"use client"`, forms, hooks, business logic, inline JSX sections, direct **`components/ui/`** imports.
- Rule: **`pages-components/<area>/<page>/<page>-page.tsx`** — named export **`XxxPage`** renders **`<XxxPageContainer />` only** — no business logic or large JSX trees.
- Rule: **`pages-components/<area>/<page>/components/page-container.tsx`** — export **`XxxPageContainer`** — all page UI logic and composition live here or in sibling **`components/<section>.tsx`** files.
- Rule: Split section subcomponents by feature or section (`hero-section.tsx`, `sign-in-form.tsx`) when JSX is long (~80+ lines) or independently owned — never split subfolders by viewport.
- Rule: When mobile and desktop need different nav widgets, keep one **`page-container.tsx`** and render sibling components with `lg:hidden` / `hidden lg:flex` — or extend the shell — never four parallel page containers.
- Rule: Page-folder encapsulation — other folders **must not** import a page's private subcomponents under **`pages-components/<area>/<page>/components/`**; move reusable pieces to **`web-app/components/<feature>/`** or **`web-app/lib/`** first.
- Knowledge: Folder naming and route groups — **`doc/web-app-pages.md`** sections 2 and 2.5.

- Knowledge: Tables in this subsection map app routes to **`pages-components/`** folders — one logical page per folder.

| Page type | App route | `pages-components` folder |
|-----------|-----------|---------------------------|
| Workspace | `app/pages/(workspace)/<name>/page.tsx` | `pages-components/<name>/` |
| User / auth | `app/pages/user/<name>/page.tsx` | `pages-components/user/<name>/` |
| Template group | `app/pages/templates/<group>/page.tsx` | `pages-components/templates/<group>/` |
| Marketing home | `app/page.tsx` | `pages-components/home/` |

### Server and client boundaries

Apply when choosing **`"use client"`** and when passing props from route files into page components.

- Rule: Default to **Server Components** in route files, page entries, and page containers — add **`"use client"`** only on leaves that need browser APIs, event handlers, or client-only state.
- Rule: Route files **`app/**/page.tsx`** stay server components — never mark a route file **`"use client"`**.
- Rule: Pass only **JSON-serializable** props from server route/page layers into client children — resolve icons and other non-serializable UI inside client modules.
- Knowledge: Input validation schemas live outside presentational components per **`.cursor/rules/typescript/typescript.mdc`** — not inside **`components/ui/`** or page section files.

### Visual design and Material hierarchy

Apply Material Design **structure** with EXL theme — not Material default purple palette.

- Rule: One primary action per screen — filled primary button; hierarchy order title → supporting text → content → actions.
- Rule: Cards — `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl`, `border border-border`, `bg-card`, `text-card-foreground`, `shadow-surface`.
- Rule: Secondary copy uses **`text-muted-foreground`**; headings use **`font-semibold`** and the responsive size scale from the layout primitives subsection.
- Rule: Merge classes with **`cn()`** from **`@/lib/utils`** — use **`buttonVariants()`** + **`cn()`** when a non-**`<button>`** control must look like a button; never nest **`<button>`** inside **`<button>`**.
- Rule: Icons from **`lucide-react`** only — size with **`size-3`**, **`size-4`**, **`size-5`**, or **`size-6`**; color via semantic token classes — no inline SVG at call sites and no alternate icon libraries.
- Rule: Wide data tables wrap in **`<div className="rounded-lg border border-border overflow-x-auto">`** — do not hide columns silently on narrow viewports without an intentional column-visibility pattern.

### Accessibility, touch, and forms

Mandatory for auth, settings, and any form-heavy page — align with **`doc/web-app-pages.md`** section 4.3–4.4.

- Rule: Smartphone form primary buttons — **`h-11`** (or size lg); optional **`sm:h-10 sm:text-sm`** on larger breakpoints for density.
- Rule: Every input has **`Label`** with matching **`htmlFor`** / **`id`**.
- Rule: Errors — **`Alert`** with **`variant="destructive"`**, **`role="alert"`**, **`aria-invalid`** on fields; loading — disable controls, **`aria-busy`** on forms, spinner on primary button.
- Rule: Password fields include show/hide with **`aria-label`**; no horizontal overflow on ~390px width unless content is in an intentional scroll container (e.g. wide tables).
- Rule: Avoid **`useMediaQuery`** / **`matchMedia`** in every page — prefer Tailwind/CSS; JS viewport checks only in shells or rare cases (drawer state, heavy desktop-only lazy widgets).
- Rule: Every list, table, card grid, or panel **must** handle **loading**, **empty**, and **error** states explicitly — spinner or skeleton while loading, centered **`text-muted-foreground`** empty copy, **`Alert`** or toast for errors — never silent failure on auth or form flows.
- Rule: Client UI shows **safe server messages only** per **`.cursor/rules/error/error.mdc`** — no raw stack traces or internal details in the browser.

### Anti-patterns — do not do

Hard stops when creating or modifying **`web-app/`** pages.

- Rule: Do not put JSX, hooks, or form handlers in **`app/**/page.tsx`**.
- Rule: Do not skip **`page-container.tsx`** or implement the full page only in **`*-page.tsx`**.
- Rule: Do not mount sign-in, register, forgot-password, or template demos inside **`DashboardShell`**.
- Rule: Do not hide primary navigation on smartphone without a sheet/drawer replacement in the shell.
- Rule: Do not create viewport-named folders or duplicate page logic per device size.
- Rule: Do not hard-code colors outside **`globals.css`** tokens or build one-off buttons/inputs when **`components/ui/`** already covers the control.
- Rule: Do not add template group routes without updating **`web-app/lib/templates/template-groups.ts`** and the templates index panels.
- Rule: Do not duplicate full auth pages at legacy paths — use thin redirect routes (e.g. **`/login`** → **`/pages/user/sign-in`**) when aliases are required.
- Rule: Do not duplicate **`MarketingHeader`** markup in **`pages-components/`** — deleted **`public-marketing-header.tsx`** pattern is obsolete; use **`components/layout/marketing-header.tsx`** only.
- Rule: Do not reference removed **`TemplatesLayout`** outer shell — template routes use **`MarketingPageShell`** + **`TemplatesPageLayout`** only.

### Auth pages and user flows

Apply when adding or changing **`app/pages/user/**`** and matching **`pages-components/user/**`** trees.

- Rule: Reuse **`AuthPageLayout`** and **`AuthPanel`** from **`pages-components/user/components/`** for consistent auth chrome — do not invent parallel auth wrappers per page.
- Rule: Link sign-in, register, and forgot-password with theme **`text-primary`** navigation links inside page containers.
- Rule: Client-side validation before submit on auth forms — distinct loading, error, and success states; no account-enumeration leaks on password-reset confirmation copy.

### Template gallery

Apply when adding or extending **`/pages/templates`** routes and demo pages.

- Rule: Register every new group in **`web-app/lib/templates/template-groups.ts`** (**`TEMPLATE_GROUPS`**, **`TEMPLATES_INDEX_PATH`** = **`/pages/templates`**) before shipping routes.
- Rule: Index page — **`pages-components/templates/components/page-container.tsx`** — Material-inspired clickable panels; must use **`TemplatesPageLayout`** inside **`MarketingPageShell`**.
- Rule: Group page tree — **`app/pages/templates/<group>/page.tsx`** (thin route) → **`*-template-page.tsx`** (entry) → **`components/page-container.tsx`** (demos) — same page-container pattern as auth and workspace pages.
- Rule: Each demo block uses **`CodeDemoSection`** from **`template-demo-kit.tsx`** — live preview, collapsible code, **Copy snippet** — demonstrate variants, sizes, and states per primitive.
- Rule: Gallery URL badge and copy affordance live in header trailing or **`TemplatesPageLayout`** breadcrumb — canonical share path **`/pages/templates`**; do not invent alternate template index paths.
- Rule: Add new shadcn primitives under **`components/ui/`** then extend a template group — do not leave controls undocumented in the gallery.

### Agent workflow — new or modified pages

Execute this checklist before marking page work complete.

- Action: Classify page type and select shell from layout shells subsection — read **`doc/web-app-pages.md`** section 3 if unsure.
- Action: Scaffold thin route, **`*-page.tsx`**, and **`components/page-container.tsx`** per mandatory page file structure — never implement UI only in the route file.
- Action: Compose content inside the correct shell using Layer 2 class patterns or primitives — responsive grids, standard padding, show/hide for optional panels only.
- Action: Apply visual design, accessibility, and touch rules on all form and auth surfaces.
- Action: Verify responsive behavior at widths **390**, **768**, **1280**, and **1440** px — navigation reachable on smartphone, no unintended horizontal scroll, auth two-column only at **`lg:`** and above.
- Action: Run **`npm run build:fast`** from **`web-app/`** before finishing.
- Knowledge: Named exports — page entry **`XxxPage`**, page container **`XxxPageContainer`**, route default **`XxxRoute`**; layout shells from **`@/components/layout/*`**, page-area layouts from **`@/pages-components/<area>/components/*`**.
- Knowledge: Recommended Playwright smoke viewports and shell routes — **`doc/web-design.md`** section 8.4 — `/`, `/pages/user/sign-in`, `/pages/dashboard`.
- Action: When adding browser E2E coverage for **`web-app/`**, follow **`.cursor/rules/playwright/playwright.mdc`** — role-based locators, no fixed **`waitForTimeout`**.

